	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style=\\"color: var(--color-ink);\\">If you serve in children’s ministry, the Father’s Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> And by “children’s ministry” we mean everyone who pours into the young — the kids pastor, the Sunday school teacher, the nursery and childcare volunteer, the AWANA leader, the VBS crew, every hand that sets out name tags and wipes tears and tells a four-year-old that God loves them. You shape eternity in people too small to thank you, often under-resourced and unseen. But you cannot hand down a fathering you have not received. The <a href=\\"https://fathersheartbible.com/read\\" style=\\"color: var(--color-brand);\\" class=\\"hover:underline\\">Father’s Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on any phone — and it reveals God as <em>Father</em>, from Genesis to Revelation. Whether you’re searching for “Bible verses for children’s ministry,” “Scripture about teaching kids about Jesus,” or simply strength for one more Sunday, it begins in one place: before you disciple a single child, you are a beloved child yourself.`}
	keyTakeaway={`Jesus said, “Let the little children come to Me.” Before you bring children to the Father, He brings you in first. You wake up tomorrow to be fathered — and the love you receive becomes the love you pass on to the next generation.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight children’s ministry carries`}
	painsIntroHtml={`Behind the felt boards and the goldfish crackers is a quiet, eternal weight. Children’s ministry is the single hardest area in the church to keep staffed, the most easily overlooked, and the place where most lifelong faith is actually decided — and the faithful few who keep showing up often do it tired, under-thanked, and stretched thin.`}
	painStats={[
