	painsBodyHtml={`<p>You serve where the applause never reaches — in the nursery while the adults sing, in the classroom while the sermon is preached, in the obscurity where no one sees the seed you planted in a child who may not understand it for twenty years. The recruiting is endless, the “just for one Sunday” that became three years is real, and the ache underneath it asks a quiet question: <em>does anyone see this — does the Father see this?</em></p><p>He does. These are not signs of weak faith. They are the symptoms of a son or daughter who has been giving to the smallest without first being filled. The God you teach little ones to love is a Father — and He is after you before He is after your service.</p>`}
