	declarationHtml={`You are a <span style=\\"color: var(--color-gold);\\">beloved son</span> or <span style=\\"color: var(--color-gold);\\">daughter</span>.<br />Not a slave. Not a servant. Not a tool. Not a performer.`}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for children’s ministry leaders`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The answer to a worn-out children’s ministry worker is not a better curriculum, more volunteers, or a slicker check-in system. It is not even more dedication. The answer is a <strong style=\\"color: var(--color-ink);\\">Father</strong> — a holy Father for a beloved son or daughter who happens to spend their Sundays loving small children.</p><p>You spend yourself making God feel safe and near to a child. But you cannot give a fathering you have not received. When Jesus said, “Let the little children come to Me, and do not hinder them,” He was making room for the small, the overlooked, the ones who cannot repay — and that includes <em>you</em>. He calls you to receive His kingdom like a child before you ever teach a child about it.</p><p>So you wake up tomorrow not first to prepare a lesson, and not first to recruit one more helper — but to be <em>loved</em> by your Father. The discipling of children is what overflows after. He is not grading your craft table; He is delighting in His child. Be fathered, and the next generation will catch the love off of you.</p>`}
