	whyHeading={`Why the Father’s Heart Bible™ for children’s ministry`}
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: `You meet the God you teach — as Father`, bodyHtml: `Every other Bible names Him “God.” The Father’s Heart Bible™ reveals Him as <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture does — from <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Genesis 1</a> onward. The simplest, truest thing you can hand a child is “God is your good Father” — and you teach it best when you have felt it yourself.` },
		{ heading: `It fills you before you pour into them`, bodyHtml: `Free to <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">read online</a> with audio on every chapter, it’s built for the volunteer’s real week — be fathered on the commute or while the lesson prints, so you arrive Sunday already full instead of scraping the bottom.` },
		{ heading: `It puts the work in its eternal frame`, bodyHtml: `“Train up a child” and “teach them diligently” start with the Word on <em>your</em> heart first. Reading Scripture in the Father’s own voice keeps your why alive — start with our <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how-to-pray guide</a> or browse the <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a>.` },
	]}
	voicesHeading={`The Father’s heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`The thing you teach the smallest child — that God loves them — these voices spent their lives proving: He is a Father:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
		{ quote: `God tenderly invites us to believe that He is our true Father and we are His true children.`, name: `Martin Luther`, role: `the Reformer, on the opening words of the Lord’s Prayer`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/b205722e3e040337b10b11b66e159abd8623472e-500x791.jpg` },
