	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for children’s ministry leaders and volunteers?`, answer: `Matthew 19:14 (let the little children come to Me), Mark 10:16 (He took the children in His arms and blessed them), Proverbs 22:6 (train up a child), Deuteronomy 6:6-7 (these words shall be on your heart, then teach them), and Psalm 78:4 (tell the next generation) all speak directly to those who serve children. Read and hear them free in the Father’s Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about teaching children about God?`, answer: `Deuteronomy 6 says God’s words should first be on your own heart, and then taught diligently to children — formation flows from the leader’s own life. Proverbs 22:6 promises that training a child shapes them for life, and Jesus welcomed and blessed children directly (Mark 10:16). In the Father’s Heart Bible™ you can read these passages free, with audio, and teach from a Father’s love you’ve received yourself.` },
		{ question: `How can a children’s ministry volunteer avoid burnout?`, answer: `Children’s ministry is the #1 area of volunteer shortage in churches, so the faithful few often serve tired and stretched. Burnout grows when you pour into children without first being filled. You cannot hand down a fathering you have not received. Many leaders begin by reading the Father’s Heart Bible™ daily simply to be loved by their Father, before they ever prepare a lesson — so they arrive on Sunday already full.` },
		{ question: `Why does children’s ministry matter so much?`, answer: `Research from Barna and others finds that roughly two-thirds of lifelong Christians come to faith before age 18, and about 43% before age 13 — childhood is where most faith is actually decided. The seed you plant in a young child may shape an entire life. That eternal weight is exactly why the one serving needs to be fathered and refilled, not just recruited and scheduled.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free online Bible with audio for children’s ministry?`, answer: `Yes. The Father’s Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on any phone or computer and read or hear any book, useful for lesson prep, devotion, or simply being fathered before you serve the kids.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father’s Heart Bible™ different for children’s ministry?`, answer: `It is the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so the God you teach children to love has a Father’s face. The simplest, truest thing you can hand a child is “God is your good Father,” and you teach it most convincingly when you have felt that love yourself first.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say to a discouraged children’s worker who feels unseen?`, answer: `Jesus said that whoever welcomes one little child in His name welcomes Him (Matthew 18:5), and your Father sees in secret and rewards what no one else notices (Matthew 6). Your hidden Sundays are not small to Him. In the Father’s Heart Bible™ you can read these passages free, with audio, and meet a Father who sees every unseen act of love.` },
	]}
